ead, the more the world opens up to you... and the happier you are and more comforted you feel. It's up to you. No you is educated who cannot educate himself.\n\n- Mark Helprin, Freddy and Fredericka\n|\nIn our civilization, and under our republican form of government, intelligence is so highly honored that it is rewarded by exemption from the cares of office.\n\n- Ambrose\n|\nAnyone can be an idealist. Anyone can be a cynic. The hard part lies somewhere in the middle—that is, being human.\n\n- Hugh MacLeod, Ignore Everybody: and 39 Other Keys to Creativity\n|\nFiction is like a spider's web, attached ever so lightly perhaps, but still attached to life at all four corners.\n\n- Virginia Woolf, A Room of One's Own\n|\nLonely people tend, rather, to be lonely because they decline to bear the psychic costs of being around other humans. They are allergic to people. People affect them too strongly.\n\n- David Foster Wallace, A Supposedly Fun Thing I'll Never Do Again:  Essays and Arguments\n|\nWithout written goals, we fail to plan and to run with single-minded purpose.\n\n- Lailah Gifty Akita, Pearls of  Wisdom: Great  mind\n|\nMisunderstanding and distrust—the predominant elements of a novel. Without them, everyone lives happily from beginning.\n\n- Carmen\n|\nYou are a dynamo, and every day offers a choice to create a life you love.\n\n- Amy Leigh Mercree, The Compassion Revolution: 30 Days of Living from the Heart\n|\nAlways work and take productive actions, do not rely on prayers and fasting alone\n\n- Sunday\n|\nWhen somebody you love dies, a phase of life’s innocence dies with that person, and a part of you dies as well.\n\n- Janvier\n|\nThe grey-rain curtain turned all to silver glass and was rolled back, and he beheld white shores and beyond them a far green country under a swift sunrise.\n\n- J.R.R. Tolkien, The Return of the King\n|\nNo, there was nothing unusual in any of these dreams as dreams. They were merely displaced in Time.\n\n- J.W. Dunne, An Experime